law.text: Every form of insurance document and every rate or other filing lawfully in use on or lawfully filed by June 18, 1970, may continue to be so used or be effective, until the commissioner otherwise prescribes pursuant to this code; except that neither this code nor the commissioner shall prohibit the use of any such document before expiration of one (1) year from and after June 18, 1970.
law.history: Amended 2010 Ky. Acts ch. 24, sec. 911, effective July 15, 2010. -- Created 1970 Ky. Acts ch. 301, subtit. 1, sec. 17, effective June 18, 1970.
